ate=November 11, 2016|accessdate=February 25, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Greg|last=Prato|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/chuck-d-on-public-enemys-two-new-albums-they-will-talk-to-each-other-20120406|title=Chuck D on Public Enemy's Two New LPs: \"fraternal twins.\"|publisher=Rollingstone|date=April 6, 2012|accessdate=February 25, 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Together Forever Tour]] (1987) (with Run-D.M.C.)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/05/20/arts/the-pop-life-two-rap-groups-plan-extensive-summer-tour.html|title=The Pop Life; Two Rap Groups Plan Extensive Summer Tour|publisher=Nytimes|date=May 20, 1987|accessdate=February 25, 2018}}</ref>\n* Check Your Head Tour (1992)  (with Cypress Hill, [[Rollins Band]], [[Firehose (band)|Firehose]], and [[Basehead]])<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Chad|last=Childers|url=http://loudwire.com/beastie-boys-check-your-head-anniversary/|title=25 Years Ago: Beastie Boys Release 'Check Your Head'|magazine=Loudwire|date=April 21, 2017|accessdate=February 25, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|first=Michael|last=Azerrad|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/beastie-boys-rollins-band-shake-up-nyc-184831/|title=Beastie Boys, Rollins Band Shake Up NYC |magazine=Rolling Stone|date=January 21, 1993|accessdate=September 6, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|first=Joe|last=Brown|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/1992/05/22/beastie-boys-rap-unchecked/96f88f7f-e415-427c-a170-65671b637406/|title=BEASTIE BOYS' RAP UNCHECKED|magazine=The Washington Post|date=May 22, 1992|accessdate=September 6, 2019}}</ref>\n* Ill Communication Tour (1994\u20131995)\n* In the Round Tour (1998\u20131999) (with [[A Tribe Called Quest]])\n* To the 5 Boroughs Tour (2004)\n* The Mix-Up Tour (2007\u20132008)\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n;[[Grammy Award]]s\n{{award table}}\n|-\n|[[34th Annual Grammy Awards|1992]]\n|''Check Your Head''\n|[[Grammy Award for Best Rap Performance by a Duo or Group|Best Rap Performance by a Duo or 