ummer-tour.html|title=The Pop Life; Two Rap Groups Plan Extensive Summer Tour|publisher=Nytimes|date=May 20, 1987|accessdate=February 25, 2018}}</ref>\n* Check Your Head Tour (1992)  (with Cypress Hill, [[Rollins Band]], [[Firehose (band)|Firehose]], and [[Basehead]])<ref>{{cite magazine|first=Chad|last=Childers|url=http://loudwire.com/beastie-boys-check-your-head-anniversary/|title=25 Years Ago: Beastie Boys Release 'Check Your Head'|magazine=Loudwire|date=April 21, 2017|accessdate=February 25, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|first=Michael|last=Azerrad|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/beastie-boys-rollins-band-shake-up-nyc-184831/|title=Beastie Boys, Rollins Band Shake Up NYC |magazine=Rolling Stone|date=January 21, 1993|accessdate=September 6, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|first=Joe|last=Brown|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/1992/05/22/beastie-boys-rap-unchecked/96f88f7f-e415-427c-a170-65671b637406/|title=BEASTIE BOYS' RAP UNCHECKED|magazine=The Washington Post|date=May 22, 1992|accessdate=September 6, 2019}}</ref>\n* Ill Communication Tour (1994\u20131995)\n* In the Round Tour (1998\u20131999) (with [[A Tribe Called Quest]])\n* To the 5 Boroughs Tour (2004)\n* The Mix-Up Tour (2007\u20132008)\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n;[[Grammy Award]]s\n{{award table}}\n|-\n|[[34th Annual Grammy Awards|1992]]\n|''Check Your Head''\n|[[Grammy Award for Best Rap Performance by a Duo or Group|Best Rap Performance by a Duo or Group]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[37th Annual Grammy Awards|1995]]\n|\"[[Sabotage (song)|Sabotage]]\"\n|[[Grammy Award for Best Hard Rock Performance|Best Hard Rock Performance]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Rowspan=\"2\"|[[41st Annual Grammy Awards|1999]]\n|\"[[Intergalactic (song)|Intergalactic]]\"\n|Best Rap Performance by a Duo or Group\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|''Hello Nasty''\n|[[Grammy Award for Best Alternative Music Album|Best Alternative Music Album]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[43rd Annual Grammy Awards|2001]]\n|\"[[Alive (Beastie Boys song)|Alive]]\"\n|Best Rap Performance by a Duo or Group\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[47th Annual Grammy Awards|2005]]\n|\"[[Ch-Check It Out]]\"\n|Best Rap Performance by a Duo or Group\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|''To The 5 Boroughs''\n|[[Grammy Award for Best Rap Album|Best Rap Album]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[50th Annual Grammy Awards|2008]]\n|\"Off the Grid\"\n|[[Grammy Award for Best Pop Instrumental Performance|Best Pop Instrumental Performance]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|''The Mix-Up''\n|[[Grammy Award for Best Contemporary Instrumental Album|Best Contemporary Instrumental Album]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[52nd Annual Grammy Awards|2010]]\n|\"[[Too Many Rappers]]\" <small>(featuring [[Nas]])</small>\n|Best Rap Performance by a Duo or Group\n|{{nom}}\n|}\n\n;[[MTV Video Music Award]]s\n{{award table}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[1994 MTV Video Music Awards|1994]]\n|rowspan=\"5\"|\"[[Sabotage (song)|Sabotage]]\"\n|[[MTV Video Music Award for Video of the Year|Video of the Year]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Group Video|Best Group Video]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[MTV Video Music Award \u2013 Breakthrough Video|Breakthrough Video]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Direction|Best Direction]] <small>(Director: [[Spike Jonze]])</small>\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[MTV Video Music Award \u2013 Viewer's Choice|Viewer's Choice]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[1998 MTV Video Music Awards|1998]]\n|Beastie Boys\n|[[Michael Jackson Video Vanguard Award]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[1999 MTV Video Music Awards|1999]]\n|\"[[Intergalactic (song)|Intergalactic]]\"\n|[[MTV Video Music Award for Best Hip-Hop Video|Best Hip-Hop Video]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[2009 MTV Video Music Awards|2009]]\n|\"[[Sabotage (song)|Sabotage]]\"\n|Best Video (That Should Have Won a Moonman)\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[2011 MTV Video Music Awards|2011]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|\"[[Make Some Noise (Beastie Boys song)|Make Some Noise]]\"\n|Video of the Year\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|Best Direction <small>(Director: [[Adam Yauch]])</small>\n|{{won}}\n|}\n\n;[